This paper is primarily focused on image classification using Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of kernels for learning feature representations, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for kernel design, which involves reducing the number of parameters and computational time, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
